/wiki/Kumamoto,_Kumamoto: Kumamoto (熊本市, Kumamoto-shi) is the capital city of Kumamoto Prefecture on the island of Kyushu, Japan.
/wiki/Daiji-ji_(Kumamoto): Daiji-ji (大慈寺), also known as Daijizen-ji (大慈禅寺), is a Sōtō Zen Buddhist temple in Minami-ku, Kumamoto, Japan. Its honorary sangō prefix is Dairyōzan (大梁山).
/wiki/Amakusa,_Kumamoto: Amakusa (天草市, Amakusa-shi) is a city located in Kumamoto Prefecture, Japan.
/wiki/Aso,_Kumamoto: Aso (阿蘇市, Aso-shi) is a city located in Kumamoto Prefecture, Japan.
/wiki/Hitoyoshi,_Kumamoto: Hitoyoshi (人吉市, Hitoyoshi-shi) is a city in Kumamoto Prefecture, Japan. The city was founded on February 11, 1942.[citation needed]
/wiki/Kami-Amakusa,_Kumamoto: Kami-Amakusa (上天草市, Kami-amakusa-shi) is a city located in Kumamoto Prefecture, Japan.
/wiki/Kikuchi,_Kumamoto: Kikuchi (菊池市, Kikuchi-shi) is a city located in Kumamoto Prefecture on the island of Kyushu, Japan. The city was founded on August 1, 1958.
